{"questionId":"2604136","questionHtml":"<p>Prove by contradiction that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, for any <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo> </mo><mo>∈</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Assume&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong>&nbsp;</em>is dependent on the assumption of truth (implied by “assume” or&nbsp;“suppose that … is true”.)</p>\n<p>Subsequent marks should be awarded independently.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;odd&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;odd&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;even&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn></math>&nbsp;even&nbsp;which is a contradiction so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> is odd&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em>&nbsp;should be awarded for any valid reason to conclude that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;must be&nbsp;odd.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>(</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>11</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;or equivalent with one side&nbsp;odd&nbsp;and one side even&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>a contradiction as LHS is even and RHS is odd&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>This&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong>&nbsp;</em>is dependent on all previous marks.</p>\n<p>Accept correct variations such as work based on&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>therefore, if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math> then&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2604136","referenceCode":"23M.2.AHL.TZ1.9","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Prove by contradiction that p2-8q-11≠0, for any p, q ∈ ℤ.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"9","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}